‚Äî
How do you get to work? When I lived in Florida, my morning commute to Miami took 1-2 hours, depending on how many accidents there were that day. üòë

These days I just roll out of bed, make a coffee, and sit at my desk in pajamas for a few hours. It‚Äôs much nicer!

If I‚Äôm shooting photos though, I‚Äôm often up before sunrise to reach a location before the sun actually rises. üåû

üöÅ Shot on DJI Mavic 2 Pro

SWIMMING WITH DOLPHINS üê¨
‚Äî
The island of Mauritius is home to some incredible underwater wildlife. Colorful coral reefs, humpback whales, sharks, and huge pods of Spinner Dolphins like these! I think @anna.everywhere wants to be a dolphin... üòÜ
‚Äî
This was actually my 2nd time swimming in the ocean with wild dolphins, the other happened a few years ago during an early morning surf session in South Africa.

SWIPE LEFT üëàüèº for a short video from this amazing experience!

#mauritiusüá≤üá∫ #dolphinsüê¨

UNDERWATER WATERFALL?! üå¥
‚Äî
This is one of the coolest things I‚Äôve ever seen! On the Southwest corner of Mauritius there‚Äôs a beautiful turquoise lagoon. The ocean floor suddenly drops 13,000 ft (4000m) creating the optical illusion of a waterfall, underwater... ü§ó
‚Äî
There are regular helicopter & seaplane flights that will give you this epic viewpoint. üöÅ
‚Äî
#mauritius #opticalillusions

DYLAN‚Äôs FIRST ADVENTURE
‚Äî
To celebrate 2 months with this little guy, @anna.everywhere & I took our first proper family vacation to the African island of #Mauritius! üá≤üá∫
‚Äî
Traveling with a baby has been a learning experience for sure. But we‚Äôre getting the hang of it.
‚Äî
It takes a bit more planning, and we have to pack more stuff, but so far he‚Äôs been doing great!
‚Äî
#babytravel #adventurebaby

VENICE BOOKSTORE üìö
‚Äî
This cramped little bookstore in Venice was one of my favorite stops.
‚Äî
Libreria Acqua Alta has books packed in every corner. There‚Äôs even tubs and boats full of books to protect them from the city‚Äôs constant flooding!
‚Äî
Keep an eye out for the store‚Äôs resident cats too. üêà
‚Äî
Does that mannequin in the background seem especially excited about books to anyone? üçÜüòÜ

#veniceitaly #bookstore

One of the many cold blue mountain lakes you can find in the Italian #Dolomites! This is Lago di Braies, probably the most famous. üõ∂
‚Äî
You can rent a wooden row-boat and cruise around its pristine turquoise/emerald waters, or go for a hike in the mountains behind the lake.

The massive Italian #Dolomites putting things into perspective. üèîü§ó
‚Äî

A quiet morning in Venice -- Italy's floating city. üáÆüáπ

If you can only do one helicopter trip during your lifetime, make sure it's the island of #Kauai! üöÅ

You can rent small boats here  and cruise along the beautiful coastline (with or without a captain). It was super fun! üö§

AURORA BOREALIS ‚≠êÔ∏è
‚Äî
Nature is pretty damn cool! Have you ever seen the northern lights in real life?
‚Äî
I‚Äôve been lucky to witness them in Iceland, Norway, Greenland, and Canada.
‚Äî
Finding and photographing them isn‚Äôt always easy though, that‚Äôs why I‚Äôve put together a free guide for you, including a video tutorial! üé•

THE ALHAMBRA PALACE - SPAIN üá™üá∏
‚Äî
I once spent a few months living in the Spanish city of Granada. It‚Äôs a very pretty place with an interesting mix of Arabic & Renaissance architecture, the snow-covered Sierra Nevada mountains nearby, as well as a community of Roma (‚Äúgypsies‚Äù) who live in caves. In fact, I even spent a night squatting in one of those caves... üïå
‚Äî
In my latest blog post, I share tips for fun things to do in Granada ‚Äî go check it out using the link in my bio! üëçüèº

CAMEL CROSSING! üê™üòÜ
‚Äî
Road trips are my favorite way to explore foreign countries. Renting a car and driving yourself allows you the freedom to stop anywhere you please, traveling at your own pace.
‚Äî
We were initially a bit worried about spending 10 days driving in #Morocco, because we heard horror stories about crazy traffic (and drivers). But we gave it a shot anyway, and had an amazing trip! üöò
‚Äî
In my latest blog post, I share tips for renting a car and driving in Morocco ‚Äî including how to deal with camel traffic jams, and getting stopped by the police. You can find the link in my bio. ‚úÖ
‚Äî
Do you enjoy road trips in other countries?

WINTER IS HERE. üêâ
‚Äî
So excited (and kinda sad) for the final #GameOfThrones season! No spoilers please, as I‚Äôm in Poland and can‚Äôt watch until after 3am...
‚Äî
This shot is from Russell Glacier in Greenland, where I started a 10 day 124 mile trek along the Arctic Circle Trail. Seeing these massive walls of ice break off and crash into the river next to me was quite an experience! ‚ùÑÔ∏è
‚Äî
The ice dragon may have melted ‚ÄúThe Wall‚Äù in Westeros, but global warming seems to be doing a fine job of it in Greenland... üåè
‚Äî
#gameofthrones8 #got #thewall #sevenkingdoms #westeros #greenland #dragons #icewall

‚Äî
Born in Poland on April 4th at 10:15am weighing 7 lbs 10 oz via c-section. @anna.everywhere and I are so excited and totally in love with this little guy. Everyone is healthy and things are going well. ‚ù§Ô∏è
‚Äî
No sleep that first night, but we‚Äôre all getting into a groove now, and Dylan is turning out to be very chill. Just like his Dad. üòú

My run-in with a notorious Mexican drug cartel in the remote mountains of Northern Mexico.

People dress up in all kinds of elaborate costumes during Carnival posing for photos around Venice's famous landmarks! üé≠
‚Äî
This is the Bridge of Sighs, ‚ÄúPonte dei Sospiri‚Äù. Constructed in 1641 as a pathway into the world‚Äôs first purpose-built prison. The name refers to the sighs of prisoners looking out the stone-windows at their last view of Venice before losing their freedom...
‚Äî
#carnevale #veniceitaly

Sunset in #Venice, with Basilica di Santa Maria in the distance. Now I see what all the hype was about! üåû
‚Äî
February during the middle of the week was a great time to visit. Not as crowded as I was expecting. Although I can‚Äôt imagine what the summer is like...
‚Äî
#veniceitaly #sunset_pics

My first time snowboarding a glacier! Earning some turns on Germany‚Äôs Zugspitze Glacier for fresh tracks... üèÇüèî

The ancient Roman Forum! Excavations to clear it took over 100 years...

The forum was the political, administrative and religious center of Ancient Rome. It was here where Marc Antony delivered his funeral speech to Julius Caesar. üèõ
‚Äî
Anyone else travel to experience history up close?
‚Äî
#romeitaly #roma

A romantic gondola ride through Venice... or a staged Instagram moment? üö£üèª‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏è
‚Äî
SWIPE LEFT ‚¨ÖÔ∏è to see what else my camera captured!
‚Äî
These shots always involve more work than it might seem at first glance. I brought my tripod along for this float trip down Venice‚Äôs narrow canals, and attached an ‚Äúintervalometer‚Äù to the camera, which triggered photos every 2 seconds.
‚Äî
For the first half of our 30 minute ride, the camera clicked away as the scenery passed by, and we tried different poses. Looking to the side, looking at each other, adjusting my posture, @anna.everywhere fixing her hair. üòú
‚Äî
Finally, when we were confident we had something useable, I carefully crawled back to the front of the gondola trying not to tip us over, packed up the camera, and enjoyed the rest of our experience. With our gondolier Valentino singing romantic Venetian songs in the background... ‚ù§Ô∏è
‚Äî
#veniceitaly #gondola

The magic of Venice Carnival! üíÉüé≠
‚Äî
Modeled after ancient Greek and Roman festivals, Carnival was a holiday that allowed regular citizens to dress up in anonymous costumes and make fun of the aristocracy without fear of retribution.
‚Äî
But it eventually backfired, allowing criminals to get away with all kinds of crimes behind the masks, and Carnival was banned in 1797. The celebration & parties returned though during the 1960‚Äôs.
‚Äî
Wandering through the confusing alleyways and canals of Venice this week with colorful characters like this was so much fun! üòÅ
‚Äî
#carnevale #venice

I‚Äôve always wanted to experience this view of St. Peter's Square from the top of the dome at St. Peter‚Äôs Basilica in #VaticanCity. Finally got the chance! ‚õ™Ô∏è
‚Äî
No matter what you think about the Catholic Church, its history & influence over humanity over the years is pretty incredible. Vatican City is an independent city-state, with a population of only 1000 citizens, and the spiritual center for 1.2 billion people around the world.
‚Äî
Climbing up the stairs to the dome is a bit of a workout! But definitely worth it. There‚Äôs an elevator that goes part of the way, but you‚Äôll still need to climb for a while either way. üëçüèº

You're never too old to play in the snow... üèÇ
‚Äî
I‚Äôve been snowboarding for about 25 years now. I started as a kid, and grew up just 30 minutes away from two ski resorts in New Hampshire. I‚Äôm forever grateful that my parents introduced me to skiing & snowboarding at a young age. I was never a big ‚Äúteam sport‚Äù kinda guy, but boy did I love racing down a mountain in the snow!
‚Äî
When I was choosing a college, my number-one requirement was that there would be great mountains nearby. And I took a year off before starting school to be a backcountry ski-bum in Montana, working nights as a short-order cook and snowboarding 5 days a week in the winter. It‚Äôs been a big part of my life.
‚Äî
Had a blast hiking for some fresh tracks down Zugspitze glacier last week, on Germany‚Äôs highest mountain! üèî

HAPPY VALENTINES DAY! ‚ù§Ô∏è
‚Äî
Everyday is an adventure with @anna.everywhere. She always puts a smile on my face. Love you Kitty!
‚Äî
Make sure to eat chocolate today. Even if you don‚Äôt have a date this year. üç´üëçüèº
#valentines #valentinesday
‚Äî
üì∑ @maefius

Just a couple with their heads in the clouds... üå§
‚Äî
I haven‚Äôt been very active on social media the past few weeks. Just got sick of posting, commenting, and all the upkeep involved. Instead, I‚Äôve been sitting in front of my computer working 8 hours a day and binging on Netflix in the evenings. üíª
‚Äî
Updating old blog posts, SEO audits, and website code speed improvements aren‚Äôt very Insta-Sexy. So ‚Äî here‚Äôs a pink salt lake in Mexico that looks like it was inspired by Salvador Dali! üé® #lascoloradas
‚Äî
I think we‚Äôll go for a walk around Verona today. Check out our Insta-Stories if you‚Äôre bored and want a virtual tour...

Kerlingarfj√∂ll was named after an old troll woman who called these colorful mountains home. One night, she failed to return before sunrise, and the sunlight turned her into stone. Or so the tale goes... üëπ
‚Äî
If you want to get off the beaten path a bit and extend your Golden Circle drive with something more adventurous, this strange geothermal area is a perfect place to stop for a half-day hike, spending the night in a cabin or the nearby campground. ‚õ∫Ô∏è
‚Äî
However because it‚Äôs in the highlands, you‚Äôll need a 4X4 to get out there. The roads are rough (and regular rental cars aren‚Äôt insured for Iceland‚Äôs F-Roads.) For more tips on hiking Kerlingarfj√∂ll geothermal area, check out my new blog post, ‚úÖLINKED IN BIO‚úÖ

One of the most beautiful beaches in South Africa, #Noordhoek Beach is massive. White sand and blue-green water for as far as the eye can see! ‚òÄÔ∏è
‚Äî
You‚Äôll find it at the end of the hair-raising (and stunning) Chapman‚Äôs Peak Cliff Drive, South of Capetown.
‚Äî
However the beach is notorious for muggings, and it‚Äôs not recommended to walk it alone.

Habana Vieja, or ‚ÄúOld Havana‚Äù was my favorite part of Cuba‚Äôs capital! The colorful old cars, the classic architecture, music in the streets. üá®üá∫
‚Äî
In recent years, Cuba has seen major changes as Americans began flooding in when the rules were relaxed. Its been a mixed blessing. Local people are able to earn more from the tourism, but it‚Äôs been so sudden that the whole country was running out of things like beer. üò≥
‚Äî
If you‚Äôre planning a trip to Cuba this year, make sure to check out my favorite things to do in Havana! New blog post, ‚úÖLINKED IN BIO‚úÖ.
Can‚Äôt visit #CapeTown without stopping by to sunbathe with the African Penguins at Boulders Beach! üêßüòé

One of the most common questions I get via email is: how did I fund my first backpacking trip all those years ago? How could I afford to travel long-term before my blog made any money? üí∏
‚Äî
Well, before I started traveling, while I was working a normal day job, I also had a ‚Äúside-hustle‚Äù writing and selling a couple of ebooks online. It was this extra income that helped me fund that first year of travel adventures! üåé
‚Äî
This isn‚Äôt the only way to earn some extra money on the side though. Watching cats & dogs. Renting out your car. Dressing up like Jesus. Selling blood plasma. Freelance bookkeeping. Assembling furniture. Running local tours. There are MANY ways if you think outside the box!
‚Äî
Go check out my latest blog post, ‚úÖ LINKED IN BIO ‚úÖ, to read about 38 creative ways to make some extra money this year.
‚Äî
Do you have any side-hustles for earning extra money? üí≤

-

One of the hunting cabins we used during our Kamchatka backcountry snowmobile expedition. We mixed it up between cabins & camping. This one came equipped with a generator and a light bulb... 5-Star luxury! üòÜüí°

HAPPY 2019! ü•≥ WHAT ARE YOUR PLANS THIS YEAR?
-
These were my 9 most popular photos in 2018. ‚û°Ô∏è SWIPE TO SEE THEM ALL!
-
It‚Äôs been a crazy year, with a lot of changes! Anna & I are expecting a baby boy in the spring! We moved from California to Texas, then on to Italy to prepare for the new addition to our family. üë∂
-
I sincerely want to thank everyone who‚Äôs been following. Whether you‚Äôre here for the travel tips, photo inspiration, or just interested in learning about our nomadic lifestyle. Your comments and emails keep me motivated to continue sharing here and on the blog! üëçüèº
‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî-
‚≠êÔ∏èMY TOP 9 PHOTOS‚≠êÔ∏è
‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî-
1. One of my favorite adventures with Anna was this road trip through Morocco, including the beautiful blue city of Chefchaouen.

2. Bertha! My beloved Jeep Rubicon. I sold her before we moved to Italy, but had a lot of fun first, including this trip to the Alabama Hills in California.

3. Just standing on a giant gorilla skull in Hawaii! It‚Äôs an awesome movie prop from KONG: SKULL ISLAND on Kualoa Ranch.

WISHING YOU A HAPPY 2019! üéâ

This is #Kamchatka, a 900-mile long Russian peninsula attached to Siberia that juts out into the Pacific Ocean. It‚Äôs about the size of California, with only 400,000 residents.
-
Kamchatka is a wilderness playground, composed of thick boreal forests, geothermically active volcanoes, and barren alpine tundra landscapes like this. It was off-limits to outsiders until the 1990s, due to its strategic importance to the Soviet military (nuclear submarine bases).
-
Read my new blog post ‚≠êÔ∏è(LINKED IN BIO)‚≠êÔ∏è to learn more about our snowmobile adventure here! ‚û°Ô∏è

Rainy day on Kauai. Still managed to get a few decent shots, despite the dreary weather. üå¶üå¥
-
For every journey, there‚Äôs often some days when mother nature doesn‚Äôt cooperate!
-
Have you ever had bad weather wreck your trip somewhere?

The Colosseum! One of the new 7 wonders of the world.
-
Rome‚Äôs most famous building once held 80,000 spectators for deadly battles between wild animals & gladiators. ü¶Åüêªüêä‚öîÔ∏è
-
There was a saying: ‚Äúbread & circuses‚Äù keep the people happy. The games kept the Roman population distracted from reality - and political involvement. ü•ñüé™
-
üì∑ F8 | 2.5 sec | ISO 200

Kamchatka! Russia‚Äôs land of volcanoes. üåã
-
This is the city of Petropavlovsk-Kamchatsky, the main city on this remote peninsula in Russia‚Äôs far-east.
-
From here we bussed to the interior, then hopped on snowmobiles to visit ethnic Even reindeer herders and learn about their way of life in the wilderness. It was such a wild trip!

It‚Äôs a #WhiteReindeer invasion! I found this guy in the Far Eastern Siberian wilderness of Kamchatka, Russia. He wasn‚Äôt so friendly... and let me know it. üòù
-
Inspired by @mads viral shot earlier this week. üéÑ ü¶å

No one truly knows why the Maya civilization collapsed.
-
Some think it was due to over-population and lack of sustainable resources.
-
Others believe it was constant warfare that led to a breakdown into chaos.
-
A third theory is that a long dry-spell killed their harvests.
-
Then Spanish invaders helped finish them off.
-
All we have left is the ruins of their impressive cities... I really hope modern humanity doesn‚Äôt succumb to the same fate. üóø

This is Verona, Italy. Our new home-base for the next few years. üáÆüáπ
-
I‚Äôve been asked why we moved here:
-
‚Ä¢ The food is amazing!
‚Ä¢ It‚Äôs very affordable
‚Ä¢ Slow paced lifestyle
‚Ä¢ Universal health system
‚Ä¢ High-speed trains
‚Ä¢ Easy access to the rest of Europe (cheap flights!)
‚Ä¢ Dolomites are only an hour or two away üèî
‚Ä¢ Family friendly & low crime üë∂
‚Ä¢ Amazon Prime works!
‚Ä¢ Fiber internet available
‚Ä¢ Pet friendly (we can take @poofythefluffycat to restaurants!)
‚Ä¢ Larger cities like Milan & Venice nearby
‚Ä¢ Mild climate
‚Ä¢ Regional airport for Europe, train to Milan for overseas flights
‚Ä¢ Tons of culture & things to do!

So that‚Äôs the gist. We had other areas in mind, but this seemed to be the best compromise for us both, and our different tastes. I wanted easy access to big mountains, @anna.everywhere didn‚Äôt want to live in a small town. üëçüèº
-
Just posted a quick walk-through of our new apartment on IG Stories if you wanna check it out! ‚úÖ

Once you get past the army of vendors at the entrance, ancient stone carvings of fearsome creatures and bloodthirsty warriors at #ChichenItza inspire awe and trigger unease at the same time.
-
The ruins are extensive, covering 740 acres. Many sections have still never been excavated. While wandering around the massive archaeological site, I kept wondering what hidden treasures lay undiscovered beneath my feet‚Ä¶
-
Read my new blog post ‚úÖLINKED IN BIO‚úÖ to learn what you need to know before visiting this amazing place!

Early morning photography session in Iceland. üì∑ Getting out into nature with my camera on a regular basis helps recharge my soul. üèî
-
Much of my job entails sitting in front of a computer for hours each day, but it‚Äôs these adventures outside in beautiful exotic locations around the world that makes it all worthwhile!
-
‚Ä¢ Camera: @sonyalpha #A7RIII (photo taken with my backup #A6500)

Of the many religious buildings I‚Äôve visited around the world, #Hallgrimskirkja in Iceland is one of the most memorable. It really embodies Icelandic minimalist design and was modeled after their rugged landscape of mountains & glaciers.
-
I definitely recommend paying the extra fee to take an elevator to the top for a colorful birds-eye-view of Reykjav√≠k too!

Kalalau Beach is one of the most beautiful places in Hawaii.
-
The only way to reach it is a sketchy 11 mile hike in, or by sea kayak.
-
The Kalalau Trail has been on my bucket-list for years, but a series of landslides blocked access during our visit to Kauai with @hawaiianairlines. I‚Äôll just have to return!
-

Got a lot of questions about my Afghanistan trip after the last post.

Yes, you can travel to Afghanistan. Women too, although I‚Äôm not sure I‚Äôd recommended it alone.

No, I don‚Äôt recommend it solo for most people. It‚Äôs what I‚Äôd call a ‚Äúblack diamond‚Äù destination. Like how they rate ski slopes. You need to work your way up to it.

This is a trip I‚Äôd been planning for years. Following local news. Tracking down obscure trip reports. Talking to others who‚Äôd been recently.
-
For example, the border between Tajikistan & Afghanistan sometimes closes without warning. For days, or weeks. Which would leave you stranded, as the road to Kabul is too dangerous.
-
The Taliban is only 20 miles away. Last year, they captured the border town area (that I entered from) for 2 weeks before being kicked out again.
-
The Wakhi people, like this man, were very welcoming and friendly. However there are less nice people not far away. The situation is constantly changing.
-
And travel in Afghanistan is tough. Just getting to the start of my trek took 2 days of driving through deserts and rivers with multiple breakdowns. Meals were basically flat bread, warm sour yak yogurt, and if you‚Äôre lucky, some goat.
-
Just wanted to share a bit behind the scenes for what went into this trip!
-
There are a few adventure tour groups that visit the Wakhan (check Google) which would make things easier. I passed one of them as I was leaving the mountains. The region does see about 100 tourists every year.

The ancient tomb of an Afghan tribal leader and his family, decorated with Ibex horns and red cloth flapping in the wind.
